[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software validation plan
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: iec_61508_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document is the Software Validation Plan (SVP) for the software element
of the E/E/PE safety-related system identified below. It is prepared in
accordance with IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9 (Software validation), and
defines all planned activities to confirm that the safety-related software
meets its specified requirements in the intended operational environment.

The SVP covers:
- Validation scope: EUC operating modes and software items under validation.
- Technical strategy: selection and rationale for validation techniques.
- Validation team roles and independence requirements.
- Validation schedule within the software safety lifecycle.
- Test environment, tools, and equipment.
- Pass/fail criteria: inputs, expected outputs, and other acceptance criteria.
- Evaluation of results and failure management.
- Confirmation of safety function compliance and agreement with the FSA.

SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields classify plan requirements as HR/R/NR/--
per IEC 61508-3:2010.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: SVP-xxx.
- Replace all placeholder text in angle brackets <...> with project-specific
  information.
- Set STATUS to "Draft" during development, "Active" once approved.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

