TITLE: Validation scope and EUC operating modes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-010
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: EUC operating modes
STATEMENT: >>>
The following operating modes of the Equipment Under Control (EUC) have been
identified as requiring software validation before commissioning:

Mode              | Description
------------------|------------------------------------------------------------
Preparation       | <Pre-operational checks, initialisation sequences>
Start-up          | <Transition from safe state to normal operation>
Automatic         | <Normal closed-loop control operation>
Manual            | <Direct operator control, safety functions still active>
Maintenance       | <Reduced-functionality mode for service activities>
<Abnormal>        | <Foreseeable abnormal conditions: e.g. partial failure,
                  |  degraded mode, external disturbance>

Each mode shall be validated separately unless a formal justification is
provided that a subset of modes is sufficient to demonstrate full coverage.
