[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Validation strategy

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Manual versus automated validation techniques
STATEMENT: >>>
The following strategy is adopted for the selection between manual and
automated validation techniques:

Automated validation shall be used for:
- <Regression tests executed on each software build>
- <Performance and timing measurements requiring precise instrumentation>
- <Boundary-value and combinatorial test sequences impractical to run manually>

Manual validation shall be used for:
- <Operational scenario walk-throughs requiring human judgement>
- <Evaluation of human-machine interface behaviour>
- <Inspections and structured walk-throughs of safety function behaviour>

Rationale: <Describe the factors driving the choice, e.g. SIL level, available
tooling, repeatability requirements, coverage objectives.>

Where automated tools are used, their qualification class (T1/T2/T3 per
IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.4.4) shall be confirmed and records maintained
before validation begins (see SVP-051).
<<<
