[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Validation schedule

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-040
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Validation schedule within the safety lifecycle
STATEMENT: >>>
Software validation shall be performed as a distinct phase following the
completion of software integration testing (IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.8)
and before commissioning. The following schedule applies:

Milestone                            | Planned Date   | Responsible
-------------------------------------|----------------|-------------------
Validation Plan issued (this doc)    | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Validation Plan approved by FSA      | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name / FSA>
Validation environment ready         | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Validation execution start           | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Validation execution complete        | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Validation Report issued             | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Validation Report approved           | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>
Commissioning release                | <YYYY-MM-DD>   | <Name>

Entry criteria for validation:
- All integration tests completed with PASS verdict.
- All Safety-Critical problem reports resolved or formally accepted.
- Validation environment verified and tool calibration records current.
- Software validation baseline established in the configuration management
  system.

Exit criteria for validation:
- All SVP test cases executed and results recorded.
- All Safety-Critical and Major failures resolved (see SVP-071).
- Validation Report reviewed and approved by the Validation Lead and FSA.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2.2(c).

