[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Pass/fail criteria

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-060
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Input signal specification
STATEMENT: >>>
For each validation test case, the input signals shall be fully defined prior
to test execution, including:

a) Signal identification: name, type (digital / analogue / serial data),
   engineering units, and the physical channel or interface used.

b) Nominal sequence: the ordered sequence of input states or values applied
   during the test, with timing information (ramp rates, step times, dwell
   periods) where relevant.

c) Boundary values: inputs at the lower and upper limits of the valid
   operating range, and at least one value outside the valid range (fault
   injection) for each input with defined limits.

d) Transient and disturbance inputs: simultaneous changes, signal noise
   levels, and foreseeable abnormal input conditions (e.g. sensor
   short-circuit, open-circuit, communication loss).

e) Tolerance on applied values: the accuracy with which each input value
   shall be set, traceable to the calibration of the signal source.

The PRECONDITIONS and STEPS fields of TEST_CASE nodes in the associated
Software Test Specification and Report shall document the complete input
specification for each validation test case.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2.2(f).

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-061
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Expected output signal specification
STATEMENT: >>>
For each validation test case, the expected outputs shall be fully defined
prior to test execution, including:

a) Signal identification: name, type, engineering units, and measurement
   channel.

b) Expected value or state: the precise value, state, or sequence of states
   expected from each safety-related output.

c) Timing constraints: the maximum allowable response time from input
   stimulus to output change, traceable to the SSRS timing requirement.

d) Tolerance: the acceptable deviation from the expected value, expressed
   as an absolute value or percentage, with the basis for the tolerance
   documented and traceable to equipment calibration.

e) Forbidden outputs: any output state that must NOT occur during the test
   (e.g. spurious actuator activation in the absence of a valid trip demand).

The EXPECTED_RESULT field of each TEST_CASE node shall document the complete
output specification for each validation test case.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2.2(f).

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-062
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Additional acceptance criteria
STATEMENT: >>>
In addition to input/output signal criteria, the following quantitative
acceptance criteria shall be met for the validation to be considered passed:

Memory usage:
- RAM usage during worst-case execution shall not exceed <XX>% of available
  RAM (reserve <YY>% headroom for stack growth).
- Flash / ROM usage shall not exceed <XX>% of available program memory.

Timing and response:
- Safety task WCET shall not exceed <value> ms under full CPU load, measured
  by <timing measurement method, e.g. hardware timer, trace tool>.
- System response time (input stimulus to safe-state output) shall not exceed
  <value> ms for any safety function in any EUC operating mode.
- No watchdog timeout shall occur during any validation test run.

Requirements coverage:
- 100% of SSRS safety function requirements shall be exercised by at least
  one validation test case with a PASS verdict.

Diagnostic coverage:
- <XX>% of the diagnostic test list shall be verified by fault injection,
  consistent with the diagnostic coverage declared in the SSRS.

Numerical tolerances:
- Analogue measurements: ±<value> <unit> or ±<value>% FS (whichever is
  greater), traceable to calibration of measurement equipment.
<<<
