[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Evaluation of validation results

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Results evaluation policy
STATEMENT: >>>
Validation results shall be evaluated against the pass/fail criteria defined
in SVP-060 to SVP-062 and the EXPECTED_RESULT field of each TEST_CASE node
in the associated Software Test Specification and Report.

The following verdicts are used:

PASS     - Actual result matches expected result within all defined criteria.
FAIL     - One or more acceptance criteria not met.
BLOCKED  - Test could not be executed due to an environmental or
           infrastructure fault unrelated to the software under test.
NOT_RUN  - Test has not yet been executed.

A validation cycle is deemed complete only when:
- All test cases have been executed (no NOT_RUN verdicts remain, unless
  formally deferred with documented justification).
- All FAIL verdicts have been resolved per the failure management procedure
  (SVP-071).
- All BLOCKED items have been investigated and either rescheduled or
  resolved.

The Validation Lead shall issue a signed validation summary confirming the
overall pass/fail status before the Validation Report is submitted for
approval.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2.3.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-071
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Failure management procedure
STATEMENT: >>>
When a validation test case results in a FAIL verdict, the following
procedure shall be followed:

1. Record: Raise a Problem Report (PR) per SSP-050 within one working day
   of failure observation, including the test case ID, the observed output,
   and any available diagnostic data.

2. Classify severity:
   Safety-Critical: The failure indicates that a safety function does not
     perform as required, or that a dangerous failure mode exists.
   Major: The failure causes incorrect behaviour that is not directly
     safety-critical but requires resolution before release.
   Minor: The failure is a non-safety-related cosmetic or usability issue.

3. Analyse: Perform root-cause analysis. Determine whether the failure
   indicates a software defect, a test-case error, or an environmental
   issue.

4. Resolve:
   Safety-Critical and Major: Software shall be corrected, a new CM
     baseline established, and the affected test case(s) re-executed.
     Regression testing scope shall be determined by impact analysis.
   Minor: May be deferred with Software Safety Manager approval and, for
     SIL 3/4, prior notification to the FSA.

5. Retest: All corrected failures shall be retested before validation is
   declared complete.

6. Notify FSA: For SIL 3 and SIL 4 projects, the FSA shall be notified of
   all Safety-Critical failures and of the proposed resolution before
   retesting begins.

Validation shall not be declared complete while any Safety-Critical or
Major PRs remain open.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2.3 and Clause 6.2.1.

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Compliance confirmation and FSA agreement

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Safety function compliance confirmation
STATEMENT: >>>
The validation shall confirm, for each safety function identified in the SSRS:

a) Functional correctness: The software correctly performs the safety function
   in all defined EUC operating modes under both normal and foreseeable
   abnormal conditions.

b) Timing compliance: The safety function meets all response-time requirements
   derived from the safety requirements specification.

c) Systematic capability: The software development lifecycle, coding standards,
   and verification activities have been executed as planned in the SSP,
   providing the required systematic capability for the target SIL.

d) Requirement coverage: Every safety function requirement in the SSRS is
   allocated to at least one validation test case, and full traceability from
   SSRS requirements to test cases is maintained in StrictDoc via
   RELATIONS: TYPE: Parent / ROLE: Verifies.

e) Diagnostic coverage: The self-diagnostic functions achieve the diagnostic
   coverage declared in the SSRS for the target SIL.

The Validation Report shall include a compliance matrix mapping each SSRS
safety function requirement to the test case(s) that verified it and their
respective verdicts.
<<<
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 7.9.2 and Clause 7.9.3.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SVP-081
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Functional Safety Assessor agreement and involvement
STATEMENT: >>>
The scope and content of this Software Validation Plan shall be agreed with
the Functional Safety Assessor (FSA) before validation activities commence.

Agreement process:
1. The draft SVP shall be submitted to the FSA for review at least <N>
   working days before the planned start of validation execution.
2. The FSA shall review the SVP for completeness and adequacy relative to
   the target SIL and the safety functions under validation.
3. Any FSA comments shall be resolved and the SVP updated before approval.
4. Formal approval of the SVP by the FSA shall be documented and referenced
   from the Validation Report.

FSA presence during testing:
SIL 2:   FSA presence during test execution is at FSA discretion; FSA shall
         review and approve the Validation Report before sign-off.
SIL 3:   FSA shall be present or represented during execution of all
         Safety-Critical test cases.
SIL 4:   FSA shall be present during all validation test execution and shall
         countersign all test records.

FSA details:
  Name / Organisation:   <FSA name / organisation>
  Accreditation:         <Certification body and scope, if applicable>
  Agreement date:        <YYYY-MM-DD>
  FSA report reference:  <Document ID of FSA assessment report>
<<<
SIL_1: NR
SIL_2: R
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: IEC 61508-3:2010, Clause 8 (Functional Safety Assessment) and
Clause 7.9.2.1.

